 It is alleged that the suspect was selling stolen jewellery when an undercover officer approached him in Henshall Street in Nelspruit on 5 April. The suspect offered to add a mortar bomb along with the jewellery in exchange for R150 000 in cash. Both the jewellery and the bomb were confiscated for investigation following the suspetc’s arrest. The suspect was expected to appear at the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court today for possession of explosives and suspected stolen property.      Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za